busdesc: Discovery, Inc. operates as a media company in the United States and internationally. The company operates in two segments, U.S. Networks and International Networks.
Discovery, Inc. operates as a media company in the United States and internationally. The company operates in two segments, U.S. Networks and International Networks.

As of December 4, 2019, Viacom Inc. was acquired by CBS Corporation. Viacom Inc. operates media brands that create entertainment content worldwide. It operates in two segments, Media Networks and Filmed Entertainment.

Scripps Networks Interactive, Inc. develops lifestyle-oriented content in the United States, the United Kingdom and other European markets, the Middle East and Africa, the Asia-Pacific, and Latin America.
ViacomCBS Inc. operates as a media and entertainment company worldwide. The company operates in four segments: TV Entertainment, Cable Networks, Filmed Entertainment, and Publishing.
The Walt Disney Company, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an entertainment company worldwide.

Comcast Corporation operates as a media and technology company worldwide. It operates through Cable Communications, Cable Networks, Broadcast Television, Filmed Entertainment, Theme Parks, and Sky segments.

Lumen Technologies, Inc., a facilities-based communications company, provides various integrated services under 'CenturyLink' name to business and residential customers in the United States and internationally.
The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc. provides advertising and marketing services worldwide. It operates through two segments, Integrated Agency Networks and Constituency Management Group.
